Build order:
Phase 1. services/ledger/ — main.rs, config.rs, db.rs, hash.rs, s3.rs, errors.rs. Models for run, event, artifact. Routes for runs, events, artifacts. Migrations 0001. S3 bucket via infra/aws/. At the end of the Phase: you can create a run, append events, store and hash artifacts in locked storage.
Phase 2. services/gateway/ — main.rs, config.rs, routes.rs, tool_proxy/, retrieval_proxy/, approval/, otel.rs. infra/otel/otel-collector.yaml. docker-compose.yml wiring ledger, gateway, Postgres, collector. At the end of the Phase: Claude Code runs through the gateway, every tool call and retrieval is captured in the ledger.
Phase 3. registry/ structure. .github/workflows/prompt-regression.yml and policy-validation.yml. Ledger models for prompt_version, policy_version, eval_result. Migration 0004. Gateway stamps runs with version bindings. At the end of the Phase: every run is tied to exact prompt, policy, and eval versions in git.
Phase 4. Ledger models for tool_invocation, side_effect, guardrail, human_approval, bias_slice. Migrations 0002, 0003, 0005. Gateway side_effects.rs extended for downstream confirmations. At the end of the Phase: full evidence model operational.
Phase 5. Ledger models for custody_event, case, export_bundle. Routes for custody, cases, exports. Migrations 0006, 0007, 0008. signing.rs. tools/verifier/. At the end of the Phase: a haruspex can open a case, link evidence, export a signed bundle, and an independent verifier can check it.
Phase 6. Harden. Custody on reads. Legal hold. Retention enforcement. Access logging. .github/workflows/test.yml and deploy.yml. Security review. Load testing. Docs.
